						               													<description>The sky is full of wonders. We are starting to understand them but not always it has been like that. The devoted people of Carcassonne, lead by superstition, would read the signs in the skies as omens, premonitions, divine messages, or even punishments from the heavens... Repent or you will all be damned.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The effect of the tiles in this mini expansion can be summarized as follows:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     A solar eclipse will fill the hearts of the followers in the area with terror. They will flee to the nearest religious place to pray for salvation: monasteries, cathedrals in cities, German cathedrals,...&amp;#10;     A moon eclipse will disband any thieves on a road, as they will fear for their lives.&amp;#10;     A comet will serve as a heavenly sign for the next player founding a new city, who will persevere in this endeavour moved by their faith. The player will be granted with up to three turns while extending this new city.&amp;#10;     A meteor shower will be a sign of luck for players. Fate will grant them the favour to choose between two tiles in their next three turns.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
